text: North Wabash Historic District is a national historic district located at Wabash, Wabash County, Indiana. It encompasses 159 contributing buildings in a predominantly residential section of Wabash. It developed between about 1846 and 1949, and includes representative examples of Italianate, Queen Anne, Colonial Revival, and Bungalow / American Craftsman style architecture. Located in the district is the separately listed McNamee-Ford House. Other notable buildings include the John Wilson House (c. 1870), Milliner House (1890), Thomas McNamee House (c. 1900), Williams House (c. 1900), Eagle House (c. 1870), and David Kunse House (1846).
